And primarily, we had done a
lot of this stuff for gifting.

00:38:18.480 --> 00:38:23.720
And we decided it was time
to start our own thing.

00:38:23.720 --> 00:38:28.780
So it was a very fun
startup, insane situation

00:38:28.780 --> 00:38:31.450
where our second
bedroom was our office.

00:38:31.450 --> 00:38:33.560
Our dining room
was curtained off,

00:38:33.560 --> 00:38:35.730
and that's where we did
packaging and ribboning,

00:38:35.730 --> 00:38:38.700
and we were storing
our chocolates.

00:38:38.700 --> 00:38:41.100
And you all will very
much appreciate this.

00:38:41.100 --> 00:38:43.690
In 2004, when we
started the company,

00:38:43.690 --> 00:38:48.150
the only way you could place
an order was via fax or phone.

00:38:48.150 --> 00:38:51.290
And our order form for
these six flavors of toffee

00:38:51.290 --> 00:38:54.780
was like four pages long.

00:38:54.780 --> 00:38:58.720
It had descriptions of each
flavor and the different box

00:38:58.720 --> 00:39:03.670
sizes, and you know,
stuff like that.

00:39:03.670 --> 00:39:08.780
We did figure out a way to
take-- and it was like checks.

00:39:08.780 --> 00:39:10.090
It was personal checks.

00:39:10.090 --> 00:39:13.800
And that was kind of it for
our first holiday season.

00:39:13.800 --> 00:39:16.180
We've grown a little bit
since then, thankfully.

00:39:18.960 --> 00:39:22.355
And one of the ways that
we've grown is into a bakery.

00:39:25.100 --> 00:39:27.380
Julie asked that I
bring some cakes today.

00:39:27.380 --> 00:39:29.810
And the cakes that I
have here, I would say

00:39:29.810 --> 00:39:33.740
are the most popular
cakes that we make.

00:39:33.740 --> 00:39:37.430
And one of the most interesting
and popular cakes that we make

00:39:37.430 --> 00:39:40.120
is the Blum's
coffee crunch cake,

00:39:40.120 --> 00:39:42.660
which I am putting
crunch on right now.

00:39:45.170 --> 00:39:47.510
It is a historic cake.

00:39:47.510 --> 00:39:49.030
And this is one of
those cakes that

00:39:49.030 --> 00:39:54.890
has an enormous amount of
emotional attachment for people

00:39:54.890 --> 00:39:56.490
who grew up with this cake.

00:39:56.490 --> 00:39:59.330
There were Blum's Bakeries,
eight different locations,

00:39:59.330 --> 00:40:01.810
in Northern and
Southern California.

00:40:01.810 --> 00:40:06.020
They were all gone
by the late '70s.

00:40:06.020 --> 00:40:10.750
And this is a cake
that I knew as a child.

00:40:10.750 --> 00:40:14.840
And it was a celebratory cake.

00:40:14.840 --> 00:40:20.550
I was asked to resurrected this
cake by a food editor in 2009.

00:40:20.550 --> 00:40:25.450
And because she was doing a
story for the Los Angeles Times

00:40:25.450 --> 00:40:28.922
Magazine that, when
you're getting married,

00:40:28.922 --> 00:40:31.130
you should be able to have
any kind of cake you want.

00:40:31.130 --> 00:40:33.610
It shouldn't just be a white
cake with white buttercream

00:40:33.610 --> 00:40:34.750
and a couple on top.

00:40:34.750 --> 00:40:37.209
Like, if you like
a hummingbird cake,

00:40:37.209 --> 00:40:38.500
you should be able to get that.

00:40:38.500 --> 00:40:40.916
If you like a coffee cake, you
should be able to get that.

00:40:40.916 --> 00:40:44.190
And she also was from San
Francisco, originally,

00:40:44.190 --> 00:40:46.210
and remembered the Blum's
coffee crunch cake.

00:40:46.210 --> 00:40:49.770
And when she said,
can you do this?

00:40:49.770 --> 00:40:51.550
I was like, oh my God.

00:40:51.550 --> 00:40:53.460
I know that cake so well.

00:40:53.460 --> 00:40:57.260
I've had such an
overwhelming desire

00:40:57.260 --> 00:40:59.590
to have that cake so many times.

00:40:59.590 --> 00:41:02.730
So it was sort of a thrill.

00:41:02.730 --> 00:41:06.150
And I tested the cake, tested
the cake, tested the cake.

00:41:06.150 --> 00:41:10.800
I did a lot of internet research
about different interpretations

00:41:10.800 --> 00:41:13.850
of the cake that had
happened over the years.

00:41:13.850 --> 00:41:16.230
And after testing about
12 different recipes,

00:41:16.230 --> 00:41:18.600
I honed it down and
created my own version

00:41:18.600 --> 00:41:19.980
of the Blum's
coffee crunch cake.

00:41:19.980 --> 00:41:23.190
And when this thing was in just
this little picture in the Los

00:41:23.190 --> 00:41:25.240
Angeles Times Magazine,
the number of phone

00:41:25.240 --> 00:41:29.650
calls we received
was amazing, amazing.

00:41:29.650 --> 00:41:33.590
And like every 60,
70, 80-year-old person

00:41:33.590 --> 00:41:37.460
would had ever eaten this
cake called, and was like,

00:41:37.460 --> 00:41:39.220
I remember this cake.

00:41:39.220 --> 00:41:40.770
I grew up with this cake.

00:41:40.770 --> 00:41:43.190
This is the most amazing cake.

00:41:43.190 --> 00:41:45.860
And we were flooded.

00:41:45.860 --> 00:41:47.430
Thank you so much
for coming today.

00:41:47.430 --> 00:41:49.230
This is a thrill, I have to say.

00:41:49.230 --> 00:41:56.647
[APPLAUSE]

